 <item> <title>Indiana to Receive $9.24 Million to Turn Around Its Persistently Lowest-Achieving Schools</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/indiana-receive-924-million-turn-around-its-persistently-lowest-achieving-schools</link>
 <description>
U.S. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan today announced that Indiana will receive $9.24 million to turn around its persistently lowest achieving schools through the Education Department&#039;s School Improvement Grants (SIG).  The funds are part of $546 million available to states and D.C. under the program.  In fiscal year 2009, states received a total of $3.5 billion in SIG support.
</description>
